{
  "doc_id": "48930",
  "text": "In addition results from our studies showed that improved professional support increased IG mother's feeling and relation to the baby, including IG mothers with caesarean birth who are particularly vulnerable. Mothers with caesarean birth are more likely to suffer from psychosocial health problems after childbirth [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] , and they seem more self-oriented and less self-confident when caring for the baby two months after birth [CITATION_4] , which may negatively influence mother-infant interaction [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] . These results point to the importance of improving professional attitudes to improve support and quality of care for mothers and families in childbirth.",
